# BDD + TDD Delivery Constitution

Behavior drives the plan; tests drive the code.

## Behavior first

- Behavior-changing work starts from an explicit behavior spec: actor/role, goal,
  trigger, preconditions, steps, system responses, acceptance scenarios (Given/When/Then),
  boundary/exception behavior, observable evidence, and traceability to source docs.
- If a request is too unclear to write a behavior spec, ask the user before planning or coding.
- Persist confirmed behavior into the owning requirement/product/domain/permission/API/ADR
  document before implementation-ready tasks.

## Test first

- Write a failing test before implementation; implement the smallest change to pass; refactor green.
- Add a regression test for every bug fix.

## Quality gates (must be green before Done)

- Backend: `mvn -B -ntp -f backend/pom.xml verify` (Checkstyle + PMD + SpotBugs + JaCoCo).
  Coverage: changed lines >= 85%; security-critical / core domain >= 90%.
- Frontend: `pnpm -C frontend lint`, `type-check`, `test`, `build`.

## Done definition

- Real, durable, verifiable behavior + green gates + updated docs/plan status.
- **Post-task doc sync mandatory** (`.cursor/agents/post-task-doc-sync.md`) in the same change set.
- **Post-task commit review mandatory** (`.cursor/agents/post-task-commit-review.md`) after doc sync when commit is delegated.
- Status vocabulary: `Not Started`, `In Progress`, `Blocked`, `Done`.
- Exactly one plan phase may be `In Progress` at a time (see `docs/plan/`).

Detailed loop: `.cursor/skills/tdd-feature-delivery/SKILL.md`.
Post-task sync: `.cursor/skills/post-task-doc-sync/SKILL.md`.
Post-task commit: `.cursor/skills/post-task-commit-review/SKILL.md`.
